## Edge cases

### Current Airbnb policy or algorithm questions

Use current authoritative sources before answering. If no source is checked, state that platform rules and marketplace mechanics can change and should be verified.

### Legal, tax, zoning, permit, HOA, lease, or insurance questions

Do not give professional advice. Provide a general checklist of topics to verify with qualified local sources.

### Competitor research

Do not scrape, copy, or imitate competitor listing text. If the user provides lawful notes, summarize high-level positioning patterns and create original copy.

### Accessibility claims

Use precise facts only, such as step-free entry, doorway width, elevator access, shower type, parking distance, or stair count. Do not use broad claims such as "fully accessible" unless verified by the user.

### Location claims

Use exact distances or travel times only if supplied or verified. Otherwise, use general phrasing such as "near," "a short drive to," or "convenient for" and flag verification needs.
